deck: An immortal knight that is the son of Galahad.  He is immortal as long as he follows the 10 virtues of knighthood.
description:
Sir Galahad was the son of Lancelot. Sir Galahad was one of 3 knights sent on a quest to find the Holy Grail. He found it and it bestowed Immortality on him. He was warned from an angel that his as long as he did not bear children and lose his knightly virtues he would be immortal. If he did have children his immortality would be passed on to them. Sir Galahad lived for over 1000 years before he fell in love. In the year of 1870 Sir Galahad bore a son. With the birth of his son he began to teach Ian how to use a sword and about the 10 Virtues of Knighthood (Courage, Justice, Mercy, Generosity, Faith, Nobility, Hope, Strength, Humility and Horsemanship).

At the age of 21 Jacob was given the @Sword of Truth and swore to protect Great Britain. Queen Victoria Knighted him after saving her grandson from Bandits. He took the name White Knight during World War 1.

White Knights Powers

White Knight is immortal as long as he doesn't bear any children. He believes as long as he upholds his knightly virtues he will live forever, although this is not known to be true or not. If enough damage is done he will stop breathing and his body will heal his wounds until it can sustain itself.

The Sword of Truth can cut through just about anything (Manchines armor has been the only thing that so far not been cut by the Sword of Truth.) It has the ability to protect its user from lies and illusions. It also can cut through to different Ley Lines around the Earth. Teleporting people from one spot to another.


Also has a number of devices on him from grappling gun, to throwing stars, lockpics and a breathing mask. He also has lightweight armor that he wears. It's especially made to stop armor piercing bullets. Along with being a Master Swordsmen White Knight has been trained in multiple martial arts and is a Master of many of them.

deck: Inmate at Riker's Island when Sela discovered Spyder was a Highborn.
description:
Origin

Spyder was originally a hooker on the streets of New York City. When she murdered and left for dead by a costumer, she transformed into a spider-like creature, returned to the streets, found her murderer and killed him. She was arrested, taken to Riker's Island, where she bullied a fellow inmate named Princess. When Sela took her role as guardian of Princess, Spyder confronted Sela in the showers with a self-made knife. Sela used the knife to stab Spyder, but thanks to her powers, Spyder survived and again confronted Sela. When zombies attacked, Spyder transformed into her spider-like form, leading Sela to the conclusion Spyder is a Highborn.
name: Spyder

deck: A student at King's Dominion High School for the Deadly Arts, and the son of Stalin's top assassin.
description:
History

Viktor's father was one of Stalin's top assassins in the KGB. British assassins tracked down his home and broke in, however, Viktor's father was not at home. In retaliation, they raped and murdered Viktor's mother. Later when his father returned home, he blamed Viktor for being too weak and beat him. Since that day, Viktor has spent every minute to become as strong as possible to not put himself in that position again.

Early in their Freshman days, Victor was teased by Shabnam during a martial arts class and was humiliated by the teacher, Master Zane. Viktor and several others ganged up on Shabnam in the showers in retaliation. Marcus Lopez intervened and defended Shabnam.

Viktor held his grudge and when Marcus was going through relationship issues with Saya, Viktor hid in the shadows to spy on Marcus as he overheard their actions at the Tenderloin. Viktor later approached Marcus with an ultimatum; he turn himself into Master Lin, or turn his friends into Master Lin for their crimes of murdering at the Tenderloin. Marcus had enough with Viktor and planned to murder him. When Viktor went on his usual morning run, he was not expecting Marcus to track him. As he entered the showers, he bent over to pick up soap when Marcus fired his gun. The shot barely missed Viktor and took off his ear. Viktor began to run for his life and pushed past Master Zane who was entering the showers and took a bullet to the head. Viktor ran to the auditorium where the school was meeting to hid in plain sight with the rest of the class. At that time, Marcus entered and hid his gun and motives as he sat down to wait out the meeting. However, they were all in shock when Master Lin announced he knew there was murder occurring within the school. He announced their new assignment was to kill those students who have killed others.

Shabnam quickly made his move and teamed up with several students who were not rats, including Viktor. He agreed to become the intelligence if Viktor would be the military and he offered Viktor a large automatic weapon a gesture of their new partnership to kill Marcus. Viktor soon spotted Marcus and his crew. However, instead of sniping them from a distance, he wanted to hunt them and give them the death they deserved.

Viktor and his crew soon tracked down Billy. Billy was left to improvise and was savagely beaten by Viktor. Viktor thought Billy was weak and lazy as he told them the story of his past. Just before he was about to kill him, Billy sprung a trap and a stone pillar crushed Viktor's back. Marcus and Petra arrived and were surprised Billy had gone through so much. They fled to the last place anyone would look -- the Tenderloin. However, Viktor surprisingly got up, bloody and battered, and was determined to kill the crew and teamed up with Dan to hunt the down.
name: Viktor
